Russia intends to sign NATO's Partnership for  Peace programme for military cooperation with the countries of the former  Soviet bloc, Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev said here Tuesday.
Speaking after a meeting with NATO defence ministers, he said Russia would  sign the programme "without setting forth any conditions." But Grachev gave no  date for the signing.
He told journalists that he would set forth the details of Russia's  proposed military participation in the programme here on Wednesday.
